YouCoded License
================

YouCoded is dual-licensed to reflect the different licensing obligations of
its desktop and Android distributions.

  • The YouCoded desktop application (Electron + React — located in
    `desktop/`), the shared React user interface (`desktop/src/renderer/`),
    repository-level build scripts (`scripts/`), documentation (`docs/`), and
    other non-platform-specific files in this repository are licensed under
    the MIT License, the full text of which follows below. A copy also lives
    at `desktop/LICENSE`.

  • The YouCoded Android application (located in `app/`) is licensed under
    the GNU General Public License, version 3 (GPLv3), because it links
    against Termux terminal-emulator and terminal-view, which are GPLv3. The
    full GPLv3 text and a preamble explaining the boundary lives at
    `app/LICENSE`.

GPLv3 Section 5 permits MIT-licensed source (such as the shared React UI) to
be aggregated into the Android application. The resulting Android .apk / .aab
distribution is governed by GPLv3, but the underlying source code — as offered
in this repository — retains its original MIT license. Redistributing the
MIT-licensed portions on their own, or bundling them with other MIT-compatible
software, does not trigger GPLv3's copyleft.

